    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ G(t) = {\frac{t^{4}-2t^{3}+t^{2}}{3t^{4}-2t^{3}-t^{2}}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>G(t)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t-1}{3t+1}, t\ne 1\hbox{ and }t\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   G(t) \amp = {\frac{t^{4}-2t^{3}+t^{2}}{3t^{4}-2t^{3}-t^{2}}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}-2t+1\right)}}{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(3t^{2}-2t-1\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)^{2}}}{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(3t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{t-1}{3t+1}, t\ne 1\hbox{ and }t\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since <m>t^{2}(t - 1)</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>t \ne {1, 0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
